version_description: Complete and well-aligned chords for the whole song / rhythm tabs for most parts.

The D in the bridge and in the end is played by moving (sliding) the C chord up a full step. You play the A, D, G strings, so the notes are D, F#, G. Hope you understand, listen to the song to get it right.
To play along the record tune your guitar down half a step.
This version is complete, but you should listen a bit carefully to get the little licks that are played throughout the song.

song_name: First Time In A Long Time Acoustic

version_description: In the unplugged version of this song, it seems that Leo Leoni plays a Em7 - Cadd9 chord progression in the bridge section. But after listening to the studio version, the Bm chord suits better there for me. You can choose which progression you use. Enjoy. :).

song_name: He Aint Heavy Hes My Brother

version_description: To play along the record, tune your guitar down half a step (or transpose the chords down half a step...). You may listen a bit carefully to get the timings of the chords.
